Full Title: Postgraduate Conference in Linguistics and Language 

Date: 05-Nov-2009 - 06-Nov-2009
Location: Ankara, Turkey 
Contact Person: Organizing Committee
Meeting Email: grad@metu.edu.tr
Web Site: http://www.fedu.metu.edu.tr/pstgrd/ 

Linguistic Field(s): Applied Linguistics 

Subject Language(s): English (eng)

Call Deadline: 04-Sep-2009 

Meeting Description:

The Conference aims to focus on, but is not limited to, the following areas:

-First/Second Language Acquisition
-Bilingualism/Multilingualism
-Sociolinguistics
-Psycholinguistics
-Pragmatics
-Computational Linguistics
-Corpus Studies
-Discourse Analysis
-EFL/ESL Methodology: teaching language skills and components
-EFL/ESL Curriculum Development: Materials and Evaluation; Program -Evaluation
-Testing, Assessment and Feedback
-ESP/EAP/CALL/ Teaching English to Young Learners
-Teacher Education
-Classroom Research
-Classroom Management/School management
-European Language Portfolio and Common European Framework of Reference 

Call for Papers:

We invite postgraduate students to submit abstracts for paper, poster
presentations and doctoral workshops on any area of linguistics and language
teaching. The Postgraduate Conference aims to provide postgraduate students with
an opportunity to share and discuss their individual research, current
methodologies and frameworks, and future directions of study.

Important Dates:

September 4th: submission deadline

October 2nd: notification of acceptance

October 9th: registration deadline

December 4th: proceedings submission deadline





